Name: College Basketball writer
about: Do you go to every Oregon home game?  Are you an avid ducks fan?  Do you have a passion for writing and want to be a reporter?  We are looking for writers for a growing college basketball website.  We want people who can write eyewitness reports after important games.  Writers will be compensated (via PayPal) for as many as 8 home games for the 2016-17 season.  Articles should be between 150-250 words in length and include at least 4 personal observations about the game's play. Please do not send photos that show the barcodes of your game tickets; we cannot be held liable for theft.  However feel free to send us photos of last year's game tickets or you in attendance of a team rally preseason game or other past game that proves you are a fan.

Name: NURSE or EMT or WILDERNESS FIRST RESPONDER 10am-4pm SATURDAY OCT 8th
about: Need coverage for 6.5 hours on Saturday October 8th   at a Private Scout Camp for kids just west of Corvallis.       PAY IS $30 PER HOUR + Mileage @ .54/per mile up to 50 miles.      You can be a:   - Registered Nurse    - EMT - Basic or above   - Wilderness First Responder      We are required to have someone with a current Oregon resident from 10am - 4pm. You will be paid for 6.25 hours if you can arrive by 9:45      IMPORTANT: You will need to provide your certification or registration number to us prior to the day as we need to add it to some safety forms about what coverage we will have at the camp.      You will not be responsible for anything other than being on site in case you are needed for a medical issue.  It's a private camp location with a small lake a lodge and various cabins.  You can stay indoors or outdoors as long as you are on site near the lake/central lodge and easily accessible all 6 hours. The central lodge has a wrap around deck that overlooks the lake so that would be ideal. You will be provided a walkie talkie for the day as well.       Some background info: the kids are supervised by their scout leaders and parents. They will be doing various activities like crafts cooking meals and using canoes. There will be a certified lifeguard and canoe instructor on duty. They have primary responsibility for the water activities you will be present as a back up. All kids must have properly fitting life jackets on prior to being allowed to start the water related activities.

Name: REQUEST FOR INFORMATION: RV moisture/mold control and weatherization
pay: please provide a non-binding estimate in response to this advertisement
about: I have a late '80s mobile home that is experiencing some moderate to severe moisture issues which have led to some issues with mold. I currently use this RV/mobile home for temporary full-time occupancy so I am eager to nip the problem in the bud.      I am currently abating the mold. However I am not comfortable performing weatherization minor roof repairs etc. that are necessary to fortify my home from rain and to reduce condensation. Therefore I am looking for a skilled person (mobile home/RV experience preferred) to provide assessment repairs and/or consultation on the issues that I'm having.       I am seeking more information about how to proceed including an initial non-binding quotation based on the information that I will provide below. If you are interested in this work please email me a few sentences about yourself your CCB# (if applicable) an initial assessment of what my needs are and a quick dollar estimate for each of the three areas below.       ASSESSMENT   Please see the attached pictures of the issues that I'm having with the roof. I have purchased rubber coating spray to cover the cracks and spaces on the roof but there haven't been enough dry days over the past 2 weeks for me to do the work myself. I wish to have the full project quoted after an on-site visit. Please provide your initial assessment of my needs as well as the cost of an on-site assessment (if applicable).      REPAIRS   Consistent with the initial assessment please provide an initial quotation/range on what repairs might cost with the understanding that a firmer quotation will happen after on-site assessment. In addition to the roof there are major moisture/rain infiltration issues around the driver door which have developed into mold. The third issue is the seals around the windows and I'm unable to tell if the pooling of water in the sills is from condensation or infiltration.       CONSULTATION   Regardless of whether repairs are necessary I am very interested in learning more about how to moisture-"proof" my home. At the very least I am looking for someone who can impart some knowledge about what I can do on my own to prevent these issues or even what they have learned from having/living in their own RV/mobile home. As a student I'm on a budget and I'm willing to volunteer my labor and assistance in the work. However YOU are the expert.          Thank you in advance for your responses!      EM

Name: Interested In Making Money Renting Out Baby Equipment?
pay: We pay you 80% of the rental fee and you keep all of the delivery fee.
about: Babierge is a national baby equipment rental service and we are looking for new on-the-ground Trusted Partners who will deliver pick-up and clean the rented baby equipment for our clients who are typically traveling families and grandparents. Our compensation works like this: We pay you 80% of the rental fee and you keep all of the delivery fee.      Ideal Trusted Partners can be described as:      - Parents with excess baby equipment   - Savvy about social networking   - Members of local parent groups and Next Door in your neighborhood   - Having a flexible schedule   - Excited to join of a new and growing business!      Here's a quick description of our company mission from our blog:       At Babierge we understand that even when traveling families require the same tools of support they use at home to raise their children. There should be no corners cut for a young family embarking on its first journeys together. As a fledgling business our number one goal is to shoulder the universal obstacles of the young family on the move. We believe the logistics and burdens of transporting an infant's necessities should not stop young families from venturing into the world as often as they'd like or worse from traveling at all.      As a young company Babierge in need of allies. Our business plan is dependent on establishing a core of Trusted Partners who will work with Babierge in their home cities to deliver items to customers and reinforce our constantly growing network of support. If making part time money alongside a loving generous and patient team aspiring to forge a new business with unfathomable potential please contact us as soon as possible!      To learn more please go to http://www.babierge.com/partners

about: This is a repost. I didn't get any replies last time but realized they may go to spam so I'm putting the ad up again.       Hello!      I need some advice on how to proceed with my roofer. I hired this roofer to reroof my home. He ended up tearing it off and then left the roof off on my home for two days and we had some very bad rain. It ended up leaking through to the interior of my home and there is water damage in numerous places in my ceiling plus a wet carpet. There is also a new leak in my laundry room that wasn't there before.       When confronted the roofer (Landon Paul roofing) told me that he is sorry but it isn't his fault and that I should expect leaks when I get a new roof as he cant control the weather. He said he tarped it (found out he tarped it Thursday morning after tearing off on a tue) and that should have kept the rain out. He denies there's any damage and he did "quality" work.       Is there anything I can do?  Do I have to pay him the rest of his money? I'm already going to have to hire someone to repair the interior from leaks plus a carpet cleaner to clean the carpet. Plus someone to redo his shoddy job. He is insured and bonded but I can't get through to anyone to make a claim at his insurance company.       Need someone with references and a lot of experience to diagnose this problem and fix the roof so there are no leaks.       Thank you!
